summary: This is an FBI evidence collection log documenting the seizure of Epstein-related case materials from the Palm Beach Police Department on October 8, 2021. The items include two bankers boxes of case materials and various physical media (CDs, VHS tape, cassette tapes).

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: The document is a log of evidence collected related to the Jeffrey Epstein child sex trafficking case. He is the central subject.

events.title: Evidence Collection from Palm Beach PD
events.description: An FBI agent collected two bankers boxes containing various Epstein-related case materials and physical media (CDs, VHS tape, cassette tapes) from the Palm Beach Police Department's storage warehouse.

locations: Town of Palm Beach's storage warehouse
keyFacts: On October 8, 2021, the FBI collected Epstein-related evidence from the Palm Beach Police Department.
The collected items included two bankers boxes of case materials and various physical media: 4 CDs, 1 VHS tape, 2 cassette tapes, and 4 micro cassette tapes.
The evidence was related to FBI Case ID 50D-NY-3027571 concerning Jeffrey Epstein and child sex trafficking.
The document indicates the evidence was held by the FBI's New York office.
